{{flavour|A ring that provides protection from the effects of poisons and venom.
----
Buttercup: “And to think, all that time it was your cup that was poisoned.”<br>Man in Black: “They were both poisoned. I spent the last few years building up an immunity to iocane powder.”<br>- _The Princess Bride_. 1987}}

The '''ring of poison resistance''' grants [[poison resistance]] when worn.

==Desirability==
Having poison resistance is very useful for certain parts of the game. [[Poison]]ous monsters are a threat from D:2, [[Lair]] is filled with them, and one Lair branch is guaranteed to be poisoned-themed. Even in [[Zot]], some form of rPois is nice to have against [[green draconian]]s and [[golden dragon]]s. Rings of poison resistance are a conveniently swappable way to get it.

{{jewellery}}
